Typedef Documentation

typedef struct bstNode * BstNode

Defines a binary search tree node type with the following:
a pointer to a char array named key
a pointer to a char array named value
a pointer to a new node of the same type named left
a pointer to a new node of the same type named right
The struct name is bstNode and the type name is BstNode

Name: fillFromFile
Type: char *filename->BstNode
Pre: a line in the specified file filename must not exceed 127 characters. The total number of lines must be an even number.
Post: reads a file where even line numbers become keys and odd line numbers become values and fills a tree with the corresponding key and value at each node red from the given file. Returns the resulting bst.
